The White House Office of the Press Secretary released a joint statement from the U.S.-ASEAN Special Leaders' Summit. The summit, held in Sunnylands, California, marked the first time a U.S.-ASEAN Leaders Summit was held in the United States. The statement reaffirmed key principles that will guide cooperation between ASEAN member states and the United States going forward. These principles include mutual respect for sovereignty, shared prosperity, commitment to democracy and human rights, support for ASEAN centrality, adherence to a rules-based order, peaceful resolution of disputes, and cooperation on global issues such as terrorism and climate change. The statement also emphasized the importance of people-to-people connectivity and collaboration at international and regional fora.